efault%2Ffiles%2Freports%2Ffiles%2FHarvard_JCHS_Americas_Rental_Housing_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20could%20strain%20rental%20stock%20supply%2C%20boost%20prices%2C%20and%20cause%20a%20jump%20in%20evictions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt's%20also%20leading%20to%20an%20insurance%20pullback%2C%20while%20premiums%20rise%20to%20meet%20the%20climate%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E41%25%20of%20occupied%20rental%20units%20in%20the%20US%20are%20located%20in%20areas%20exposed%20to%20severe%20climate-related%20threats%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freports%2Ffiles%2FHarvard_JCHS_Americas_Rental_Housing_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20Harvard's%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20about%2018.2%20million%20units%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20substantial%20loss%20damage%2C%20whether%20from%20hurricanes%2C%20wildfires%2C%20floods%2C%20earthquakes%20and%20similar%20hazards.%20That%20accounts%20for%2035%25%20to%2040%25%20of%20multifamily%20buildings%2C%20and%2045%25%20of%20single-family%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNotably%2C%20newer%20rental%20units%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20weather-%20and%20climate-related%20hazards.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20rentals%20built%20in%202000%20or%20later%20are%20located%20in%20areas%20with%20substantial%20losses%2C%20double%20the%2024%20percent%20of%20rentals%20built%20before%201940%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said%2C%20citing%20that%2052%25%20of%20manufactured%20units%20are%20at%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20older%20rental%20stock%20has%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20inadequacies%2C%20leaving%20them%20also%20vulnerable%20to%20environmental%20damage.%20US%20rental%20supply%20is%20now%20at%20its%20oldest%20level%20ever%2C%20with%20millions%20of%20rental%20units%20deficient%20in%20some%20form.%20Energy%20upgrades%20are%20also%20needed%20as%20rising%20temperatures%20and%20changing%20weather%20boost%20renter%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20limit%20future%20threats%2C%20the%20report%20emphasized%20a%20need%20to%20invest%20in%20pre-disaster%20mitigation%20and%20adaptation%20strategies%2C%20helping%20ensure%20that%20the%20dwindling%20stock%20of%20rental%20housing%20doesn't%20fall%2C%20and%20curb%20evictions%20and%20rent%20increases%20that%20typically%20follow%20climate-related%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%2028%20climate%20events%20cost%20%2492.9%20billion%2C%20though%20this%20estimate%20may%20rise%2C%20a%20January%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climate.gov%2Fnews-features%2Fblogs%2Fbeyond-data%2F2023-historic-year-us-billion-dollar-weather-and-climate-disasters%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20NOAA%20National%20Centers%20for%20Environmental%20Information%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20translating%20to%20higher%20insurance%20costs%20for%20both%20renters%20and%20homeowners%2C%20as%20well%20as%20less%20coverage%2C%20as%20insurers%20retreat%20from%20high-cost%20communities.%20Housing%20markets%20are%20still%20adjusting%2C%20with%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fhome-values-collapse-climate-change-risks-insurance-market-first-street-2023-9%5C%22%3E39%20million%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20insured%20at%20prices%20that%20don't%20reflect%20today's%20climate%20hazards%2C%20First%20Street%20Foundation%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate-related%20risks%20could%20also%20come%20to%20eventually%20batter%20down%20home%20values%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhousing-market-crash-correction-2008-comparison-market-mispriced-big-short-2023-4%5C%22%3E20%25%20of%20the%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20risk%