%20still%20below%20its%20long-term%20average%20of%2053.6%2C%20but%20it's%20moving%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20new%20business%20jumped%20for%20the%20third%20month%20in%20a%20row%2C%20and%20export%20orders%20saw%20their%20first%20expansion%20in%20five%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20percentage%20of%20economies%20with%20expanding%20services%20sectors%20jumped%20ten%20points%20to%2077%25%2C%20the%20highest%20share%20in%20six%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20maintained.%20%26quot%3BThis%20puts%20our%20breadth%20measure%20closer%20to%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20when%20global%20expansions%20typically%20saw%20services%20breadth%20at%2085%25%20or%20higher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20all%20countries%2C%20emerging%20markets%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-us-trade-markets-investors-policy-beijing-finance-outlook-2024-1%5C%22%3Eoutside%20of%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20seen%20the%20strongest%20growth%2C%20with%20India%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20leading%20the%20way.%20The%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20UK%2C%20and%20China%20are%20seeing%20%26quot%3Bmoderately%20constructive%26quot%3B%20growth%2C%20the%20firm%20said%2C%20while%20Canada%20and%20the%20eurozone%20are%20seeing%20weaker%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20in%20particular%20saw%20its%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20composite%20PMI%20hit%2052.0%20in%20January%2C%20a%20six-month%20high.%20US%20manufacturing%20grew%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20nine%20months%2C%20and%20by%20its%20widest%20margin%20in%20more%20than%20a%20year%2C%20NDR%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20supply%20chain%20snags%20have%20picked%20up%20amid%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-outlook-goldman-sachs-red-sea-shipping-inflation-federal-reserve-2024-1%5C%22%3ERed%20Sea%20crisis%20and%20the%20disruptions%20to%20global%20shipping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20prices%20have%20remained%20resilient%20so%20far%