3BLast%20night%20was%20a%20setback%20but%20democracy%20is%20messy%2C%20we%20live%20in%20a%20time%20of%20divided%20government%2C%20we%20have%20a%20razor-thin%20margin%20here%2C%20and%20every%20vote%20counts%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.c-span.org%2Fvideo%2F%3F533456-1%2Fspeaker-johnson-mayorkas-impeachment-vote-defeat%26_gl%3D1*tvszyo*_ga*NzAwMTUyODkxLjE2ODc0NTc2NDA.*_ga_MZ1V6F99FJ*MTcwNzMyOTM4My4xMDUuMS4xNzA3MzMzODMyLjAuMC4w%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJohnson%20told%20reporters%20on%20Wednesday%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20when%20you're%20counting%20votes%20and%20people%20show%20up%20when%20they%20are%20not%20expected%20to%20be%20in%20the%20building%2C%20it%20changes%20the%20equation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20Capitol%2C%20Senate%20Minority%20Leader%20Mitch%20McConnell%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcconnell-trump-immigration-ukraine-deal-mike-johnson-congress-republicans-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efacing%20increasing%20calls%20for%20him%20to%20step%20aside%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20conservatives%20nuked%20a%20bipartisan%20border%20security-Ukraine%20aid%20deal%20that%20some%20Republicans%20themselves%20said%20they%20had%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20we've%20been%20talking%20about%20the%20border%20is%20because%20they%20wanted%20to%2C%20the%20persistent%20critics%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F02%2F07%2Fmcconnell-gop-rebellion-border-deal-00139972%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcConnell%20told%20Politico%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20pass%20a%20bill%20without%20dealing%20with%20a%20Democratic%20president%20and%20a%20Democratic%20Senate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20is%20not%20the%20sole%20cause%20but%20he%20has%20exacerbated%20the%20GOP's%20problems.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20looms%20over%20everything.%20He%20is%20an%20all-consuming%20force%20that%20has%20reigned%20over%20American%20politics%20since%20shortly%20after%20he%20announced%20his%202016%20presidential%20campaign.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20was%20Trump%20who%20instructed%20Republicans%20to%20kill%20the%20bipartisan%20immigration%20deal%20before%20the%20text%20was%20actually%20released.%20The%20former%20president%20has%20also%20cheered%20on%20efforts%20to%20wield%20impeachment%2C%20one%20of%20Congress'%20most%20powerful%20actions%2C%20as%20a%20cudgel%2C%20surmising%20that%20since%20Democrats%20impeached%20him%20twice%20it%20is%20only%20fair%20to%20respond%20with%20retribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20it's%20not%20Trump%20alone.%20Hyperpartisanship%20was%20spreading%20long%20before%20his%20arrival.%20And%20with%20it%2C%20came%20the%20decline%20of%20split-ticket%20voting%20and%20perhaps%20the%20belief%20that%20good%20policy%20could%20come%20from%20sweeping%20bipartisan%20compromises.%20(I'm%20required%20to%20note%20that%20while%20that%20era%20produced%20policies%20that%20forever%20changed%20American%20life%2C%20such%20as%20The%20Americans%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%2C%20it%20also%20spawned%20the%20Iraq%20War%2C%20which%20is%20now%20widely%20viewed%20as%20a%20foreign%20policy%20disaster.%20There%20was%20no%20unalloyed%20%26quot%3BGolden%20Age.%26quot%3B)%20The%20Tea%20Party's%20rise%20in%20response%20to%20George%20W.%20Bush-era%20Republicanism%20sent%20a%20generation%20of%20lawmakers%20to%20Washington%20ready%20to%20fuck%20shit%20up%20even%20if%20it%20was%20not%20entirely%20clear%20how%20they%20would%20achieve%20their%20goals%20or%20if%20the%20tactics%20(threatening%20the%20full%20faith%20and%20credit%20of%20the%20nation)%20were%20worth%20the%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongressional%20leaders%20also%20lost%20power%20along%20the%20way.%20Freshmen%20lawmakers%20used%20the%20new%20media%20environment%20to%20build%20platforms%20that%20surpassed%20the%20elder%20leaders%20that%20were%20handing%20out%20directions.%20Not%20all%20of%20this%20change%20was%20bad%2C%20but%20collectively%2C%20as%20has%20been%20documented%20extensively%2C%20the%20current%20reality%20is%20undeniably%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPolitics%20used%20to%20be%20the%20art%20of%20the%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Mitt%20Romney%2C%20a%20Utah%20Republican%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F02%2F06%2F2024%2Fborder-bill-collapses%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20reporters%2C%20per%20Semafor.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BNow%20it's%20the%20art%20of%20the%20impossible.%20We've%20gone%20from%20the%20sublime%20to%20the%20ridiculous.%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20story%20of%20one%20senator%20tells%20it%20all.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20James%20Lankford%20of%20Oklahoma%20might%20serve%20as%20the%20best%20example%20of%20this.%20Lankford%2C%20a%20former%20congressman%20and%20youth%20pastor%2C%20is%20a%20staunch%20conservative.%20He%20is%20also%20not%20an%20outspoken%20iconoclast%20like%20some%20of%20his%20colleagues.%20It%20made%20sense%20that%20McConnell%20would%20tap%20him%20to%20be%20the%20lead%20Republican%20on%20the%20bipartisan%20border-Ukraine%20deal.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELankford%20co-produced%20a%20package%20with%20some%20of%20the%20most%20conservative%20immigration%20policies%20that%20leading%20Democrats%2C%20including%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20have%20ever%20supported.%20He%20even%20brought%20along%20the%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%2C%20once%20the%20gold%20standard%20for%20GOP%20policies%2C%20and%20the%20Border%20Patrol%20Union%2C%20the%20latter%20of%20which%20endorsed%20Trump%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20bill%20was%20even%20released%2C%20the%20Oklahoma%20Republican%20party%20formally%20censured%20Lankford.%20Half-truths%20and%20outright%20lies%20about%20the%20legislation%20spread%20through%20conservative%20media.%20Trump%20and%20even%20a%20few%20Republicans%2