3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F04165732%2FUntitled-design-2021-08-04T165720.758.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Uttarakhand%20assembly%20passed%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Bill%20on%20February%207%20(Wednesday)%2C%20aimed%20at%20replacing%20the%20religious%20personal%20laws%20governing%20marriage%2C%20relationships%2C%20and%20inheritance%2C%20among%20other%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%2C%20it%20becomes%20the%20first%20state%20to%20implement%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20comes%20just%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20crucial%20item%20on%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20independence%2C%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20Constitution%20gave%20the%20right%20under%20Article%2044%20that%20the%20states%20can%20also%20introduce%20the%20UCC%20at%20appropriate%20time%E2%80%A6%20People%20have%20doubts%20regarding%20this.%20We%20made%20the%20draft%20as%20per%20the%20constitutional%20system%2C%E2%80%9D%20chief%20minister%20Pushkar%20Singh%20Dhami%20said%20in%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssam%20and%20Gujarat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Fgujarat-government-likely-to-support-uniform-civil-code%2Farticleshow%2F101056164.cms%5C%22%3Ehave%20also%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Ftribals-to-be-exempted-from-uniform-civil-code-in-assam-himanta-101704999478670.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20states%20will%20be%20supporting%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20opposing%20views%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttarakhand%20leader%20of%20opposition%20Yashpal%20Arya%20said%20that%20the%20opposition%20should%20have%20been%20given%20some%20time%20to%20prepare%20to%20debate%20before%20passing%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%E2%80%99s%20the%20haste%20behind%20implementing%20it%3F%20We%20have%20sufficient%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20expect%20us%20to%20read%20such%20a%20lengthy%20document%2C%20which%20was%20submitted%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20ago%2C%20and%20start%20the%20discussion.%20It%20looks%20like%20the%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20hide%20something%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20full%20majority%20to%20pass%20the%20Bill%2C%20but%20it%20would%20have%20been%20better%20to%20give%20the%20Opposition%20some%20time%20to%20prepare%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20government%20formed%20the%20Justice%20Ranjana%20Prakash%20Desai%20Committee%20to%20develop%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code.%20However%2C%20despite%20submitting%20its%20report%20within%2013%20months%2C%20the%20committee%20did%20not%20publicly%20disclose%20its%20blueprint%20or%20engage%20with%20social%20groups%20or%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20this%20lack%20of%20transparency%20prevented%20stakeholders%2C%20including%20the%20Congress%20party%2C%20from%20providing%20inputs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Congress%20party%20wrote%20letters%20to%20the%20committee%20twice%2C%20asking%20for%20the%20draft%2C%20but%20the%20committee%20did%20not%20give%20any%20reply.%20In%20a%20country%20where%20many%20laws%2C%20including%20criminal%20laws%2C%20are%20still%20not%20uniform%2C%20how%20can%20anyone%20give%20their%20views%20on%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20imagination%20only%3F%20If%20the%20committee%20had%20given%20a%20blueprint%2C%20many%20practical%20and%20valuable%20ideas%20would%20have%20come%20to%20the%20fore%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20on%20X%20in%20Hindi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20come%20to%20light%20through%20the%20press%20that%20your%20law%20