the%20December%20quarter%2C%20the%20FMCG%20sector%20grew%206.4%25%20in%20volumes%20on%20the%20back%20of%20positive%20consumption%20across%20the%20country%2C%20NielsenIQ%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rate%20of%20consumption%20growth%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20both%20volume%20and%20value%2C%20within%20the%20FMCG%20sector%20decelerated%20sequentially%20across%20the%20entire%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20was%20seen%20in%20both%20urban%20and%20rural%20markets%2C%20where%20volumes%20grew%20year-on-year%20but%20dipped%20sequentially%2C%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Findustry%2Fretail%2Ffmcg-industry-s-growth-this-year-could-halve-from-2023-says-nielseniq-11707206179710.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20volume%20growth%20in%20the%20urban%20sector%20during%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20stood%20at%206.8%25%20as%20compared%20to%2010.2%25%20in%20the%20previous%20quarter.%20Rural%20volume%20growth%20stood%20at%205.8%25%20against%206.4%25%20in%20the%20July%20to%20September%20quarter%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fretail.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Ffood-entertainment%2Fpersonal-care-pet-supplies-liquor%2Fdec-quarter-sees-6-4-surge-in-fmcg-volumes-urban-rural-gap-narrows-report%2F107455176%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20value%20growth%20in%20the%20industry%20stood%20at%206%25%20in%20the%20quarter.%20This%20has%20been%20attributed%20to%20the%206.4%25%20rise%20in%20volume.%20Therefore%2C%20this%20indicates%20positive%20consumption%20patterns%20at%20an%20all-India%20level%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20added%20that%20the%20volume%20growth%20in%20the%20food%20sector%20during%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20stood%20at%205.3%25%2C%20down%20from%208.7%25%20in%20the%20July-September%20quarter%20of%202023.%20This%20was%20attributed%20to%20the%20slowdown%20in%20the%20products%20under%20staples%20(such%20as%20refined%20and%20non-refined%20edible%20oils%2C%20etc.)%20and%20impulse%20(such%20as%20confectionery%2C%20etc.)%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20non-food%20categories%2C%20which%20include%20personal%20and%20home%20care%20products%2C%20there%20is%20an%20improvement%2C%20with%20volume%20growth%20reaching%209.6%25%20in%20the%20quarter%20ended%20December%20as%20compared%20to%20last%20year.%20This%20is%20an%20increase%20from%20the%208.7%25%20recorded%20in%20July-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20growth%20in%20terms%20of%20volume%20refers%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20physical%20quantity%20of%20goods%20sold%20over%20a%20specific%20period%2C%20irrespective%20of%20changes%20in%20pricing.%20This%20reflects%20the%20actual%20demand%20for%20the%20products.%20This%20aspect%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20consumer%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20growth%20in%20value%20terms%20refers%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20sales%20revenue%20or%20market%20value%20of%20FMCG%20products%20over%20a%20specific%20period.%20It%20takes%20into%20account%20factors%20such%20as%20price%20increases.%20It%20indicates%20how%20well%20a%20company%20is%20performing%20in%20terms%20of%20generating%20revenue%20from%20its%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENarrowing%20rural-urban%20gap%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20the%20anticipated%20slowdown%2C%20Nielsen%20remains%20optimistic%20about%20the%20FMCG%20industry%E2%80%99s%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoosevelt%20Dsouza%2C%20head%20of%20customer%20success%20at%20NielsenIQ%20India%2C%20despite%20a%20sequential-quarter%20decline%2C%20the%20rural%20recovery%20narrative%20continued%20to%20evolve%20throughout%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20highlighted%20that%20in%202023%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20consumption%20gaps%20between%20urban%20and%20rural%20markets%20narrowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20northern%20and%20western%20regions%20are%20contributing%20to%20this%20phenomenon.%20The%20favourable%20interim%20Union%20Budget%202024-25%2C%20supporting%20several%20economic%20boosters%20for%20the%20rural%20sector%2C%20should%20augur%20well%20for%20companies%20with%20a%20rural%20strategy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dsouza%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Q4%202023%2C%20we%20observe%20an%20uptick%20in%20consumption%2C%20primarily%20driven%20by%20habit-forming%20categories%20(such%20as%20biscuits%20and%20noodles)%20in%20food%20and%20essential%20home%20products.%20These%20categories%20have%20thrived%20despite%20flat%20to%20negative%20price%20growth%2C%20indicating%20resilience%20and%20sustained%20demand%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Frising-thali-cost-muted-fmcg-growth-booming-luxury-sales-why-the-k-shaped-recovery-still-stands%5C%22%3ERising%20Thali%20Cost%2C%20Muted%20Fmcg%20Growth%2C%20Booming%20Luxury%20Sales%3A%20Why%20the%20K-Shaped%20Recovery%20Still%20Stands%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20FMCG%20firms%20say%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20slowdown%20in%20rural%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Findustry%2Fretail%2Ffmcg-industry-s-growth-this-year-could-halve-from-2023-says-nielseniq-11707206179710.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20market%20analysts%20expressing%20their%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFMCG%20companies%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20a%20persistent%20slowdown%20in%20rural%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20definite%20slowdown%2C%E2%80%9D%20Krishnarao%20Buddha%2C%20senior%20category%20head%2C%20marketing%20at%20Parle%20Products%20told%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CBoth%20rural%20and%20urban%20markets%20have%20slowed%20down.%20Errant%20monsoon%20in%20select%20geographies%20due%20to%20the%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%20has%20impacted%20slowdown%20in%20consumption.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20normalizing%20effect%20post-COVID%2C%E2%80%9D%20Buddha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COverall%20sector%20growth%20continues%20to%20wane%2C%20with%20price%20growth%20turning%20negligible.%20Urban%20growth%20has%20seen%20moderation%20and%20is%20now%20growing%201.2X%20rural.%20The%20low%20base%20aids%20non-food%20volume%20recovery%2C%20while%20food%20categories%20are%20seeing%20volume%20growth%20moderation.%20Channel%20growth%20has%20moderated%2C%20but%20modern%20trade%20continues%20to%20clock%20healthy%20growth%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nitin%20Gupta%20of%20Emkay%20Global%20Financial%20Services%2C%20told%20the%20business%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fmore-inventory-days-for-consumer-goods-as-low-demand-causes-supply-chain-congestion%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20persistent%20low%20demand%20in%20the%20FMCG%20sector%20is%20causing%20supply%20chain%20congestion%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20inventory%20days%2C%20with%20stocks%20accumulating%20at%20distributors.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707305401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15171005%2F1024px-Supermarket_full_of_goods.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ffmcg-growth-slows-sequentially-in-december-quarter-expected-to-slow-to-4-5-6-5-in-2024-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20volume%20growth%20in%20the%20urban%20sector%20during%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20stood%20at%206.8%25%20as%20compared%20to%2010.2%25%20in%20the%20previous%20quarter.%20Rural%20volume%20growth%20stood%20at%205.8%25%20against%206.4%25%20in%20the%20July%20to%20September%20quarter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2