%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Anand%20also%20started%20to%20visit%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F338824%2Fmuskaan-dreams-abhishek-dubey-introduces-technology-in-rural-school-education-digital-literacy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20schools%20for%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20visual%20impairment%20across%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Victoria%20Memorial%20School%20for%20the%20Blind%20in%20Mumbai%20left%20a%20lasting%20impression%20on%20me%20because%20of%20its%20remarkable%20beauty%2C%20despite%20being%20an%20adaptively%20reused%20building.%20However%2C%20I%20found%20very%20few%20good%20examples%20of%20schools%20specifically%20designed%20for%20users%20with%20disabilities.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20I%20later%20volunteered%20at%20the%20Perkins%20School%20for%20the%20Blind%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20one%20of%20the%20oldest%20schools%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Established%20in%201829%2C%20it%20boasts%20a%20rich%20history%20with%20stalwarts%20like%20Helen%20Keller%2C%20Laura%20Bridgman%2C%20and%20Anne%20Sullivan%20who%20all%20studied%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20found%20wonderful%20mentors%20in%20the%20US%20and%20was%20able%20to%20find%20the%20right%20direction%20for%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20went%20out%20looking%20for%20inspiration%2C%20I%20realised%20how%20it%20was%20not%20one%20place%20that%20could%20help%20me%20but%20a%20lot.%20Visiting%20various%20schools%20was%20a%20great%20learning%20arc%20for%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EUsing%20five%20senses%20to%20navigate%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20school%20is%20designed%20to%20be%20navigated%20with%20the%20help%20of%20four%20senses%3A%20sight%2C%20hearing%2C%20touch%2C%20and%20smell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnly%2015%25%20of%20people%20with%20blindness%20experience%20a%20complete%20lack%20of%20sight.%20The%20majority%20of%20individuals%20who%20are%20blind%20may%20perceive%20light%20or%20colour%2C%20and%20those%20with%20different%20impairments%20have%20varying%20degrees%20of%20usable%20vision%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-4-1706623360.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20school%20walls%20have%20different%20textures%20for%20students%20to%20recognise%20the%20classes.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-4-1706623360.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-4-1706623360-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-4-1706623360-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-4-1706623360-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-4-1706623360-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-340122%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20school%20walls%20have%20different%20textures%20for%20students%20to%20recognise%20the%20classes.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20Anand%20designed%20a%20school%20that%20uses%20colour%2C%20smell%2C%20and%20light%20to%20distinguish%20each%20class.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETouch%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20employed%20five%20different%20types%20of%20wall%20plasters%20and%20textures%20for%20students%20to%20identify%20spaces.%20Additionally%2C%20for%20ease%20of%20navigation%2C%20we%20utilised%20different%20textures%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20incorporating%20rough%20and%20smooth%20Kota%20stone%2C%20which%20marks%20the%20entry%20points%20of%20the%20classrooms%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20area%20classroom%2C%20corridor%2C%20and%20courtyard%20in%20the%20school%20is%20marked%20and%20written%20in%20Braille.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHearing%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20another%20navigation%20technique%20that%20utilises%20hearing%2C%20Anand%20varies%20the%20volumes%20and%20heights%20of%20the%20buildings%2C%20creating%20different%20echoes%20and%20sounds%20to%20assist%20students%20in%20identifying%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20the%20entrance%20of%20the%20school%20features%20a%20wide%20and%20tall%20volume%2C%20while%20the%20opposite%20side%20has%20a%20shorter%20volume%20and%20is%20narrower.%20This%20contrast%20in%20width%20and%20height%20produces%20a%20distinct%20echo%20compared%20to%20the%20entrance.%20Students%2C%20as%20part%20of%20their%20training%2C%20walk%2C%20talk%2C%20and%20even%20clap%20to%20practise%20using%20different%20techniques%20for%20identifying%20spaces%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20navigation%20easy%20for%20students%20who%20can%20perceive%20colour%20in%20light%2C%20he%20used%20different%20colours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20that%20many%20low%20vision%20students%20are%20studying%20in%20the%20school%2C%20another%20aspect%20we%20had%20to%20consider%20was%20using%20contrasting%20colours%20and%20lighting%20to%20help%20students%20identify%20objects%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F320628%2Fheta-pandit-writes-stories-from-goan-homes-book-on-culture-family-food%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurniture%2C%20and%20spaces%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20each%20classroom%20door%20is%20brightly%20painted%2C%20the%20entrance%20is%20in%20a%20different%20bright%20colour%2C%20and%20the%20toilet%20doors%20are%20painted%20in%20contrasting%20yet%20vibrant%20colours.%20This%20approach%20ensures%20that%20students%20with%20low%20vision%20can%20readily%20identify%20and%20locate%20important%20elements%2C%20such%20as%20the%20switchboard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmell%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20to%20make%20the%20classrooms%20even%20more%20distinctive%20from%20each%20other%2C%20the%20architect%20decided%20to%20engage%20the%20sense%20of%20smell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20also%20planted%20aromatic%20plants%20at%20entries%2C%20which%20can%20assist%20students%20in%20marking%20and%20identifying%20places.%20These%20elements%20serve%20as%20different%20clues%20incorporated%20into%20our%20design.%20Students%2C%20based%20on%20their%20comfort%20and%20understanding%2C%20use%20these%20clues%20to%20navigate%20the%20building.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-5-1706623443.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20school%20has%20brightly%20coloured%20doors%20to%20help%20the%20students%20with%20partial%20vision%20navigate%20better.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-5-1706623443.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-5-1706623443-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-5-1706623443-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-5-1706623443-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-5-1706623443-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-340124%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20school%20has%20brightly%20coloured%20doors%20to%20help%20the%20students%20with%20partial%20vision%20navigate%20better.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EInclusive%2C%20sustainable%20and%20a%20haven%20for%20the%20students%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20five%20special%20classrooms%20and%20seven%20classrooms%20with%20individual%20courtyards%20in%20the%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20furniture%20arrangement%20was%20also%20crucial%2C%20and%20the%20shape%20and%20size%20of%20the%20classrooms%20evolved%20based%20on%20how%20students%20would%20sit.%20To%20ensure%20equal%20attention%20from%20the%20teacher%2C%20we%20designed%20a%20%E2%80%98C%E2%80%99%20shaped%20seating%20arrangement%20where%20each%20student%20is%20in%20close%20proximity%20to%20the%20teacher%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnand%20also%20believed%20that%20the%20children%20should%20also%20get%20the%20chance%20to%20learn%20outdoors%2C%20hence%20he%20included%20the%20courtyards.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20recognised%20that%20learning%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20only%20happen%20within%20the%20classroom%20but%20extends%20beyond%20its%20walls.%20Considering%20this%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20courtyards%20became%20crucial.%20In%20addition%20to%20their%20educational%20significance%2C%20there%20were%20practical%20reasons%20for%20incorporating%20courtyards%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20area%20experiences%20a%20hot%20and%20dry%20climate%2C%20which%20can%20be%20challenging%20for%20students%20with%20low%20vision%20sensitive%20to%20direct%20light.%20To%20address%20this%2C%20we%20ensured%20that%20the%20courtyard%20provides%20filtered%20light%20to%20the%20classrooms%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndirect%20light%20was%20a%20significant%20concern%20as%20the%20architect%20aimed%20to%20provide%20a%20comfortable%20learning%20environment%20for%20low-vision%20students%20with%20minimal%20glare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20protect%20the%20low-vision%20students%20from%20direct%20light%20glare%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F318714%2Ftamil-nadu-engineer-turns-artist-paints-with-sunlight-vignesh%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebring%20sunlight%20from%20the%20roof%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20not%20from%20windows%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20haven%20for%20its%20students%2C%20the%20school%20also%20is%20sustainable%20in%20its%20roots.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20decided%20to%20be%20very%20frugal%20with%20what%20we%20were%20using.%20We%20used%20only%20locally-sourced%20materials%20such%20as%20Kota%20stone%20and%20planted%20more%20than%201%2C000%20plants%20of%2037%20different%20varieties%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-6-1706623850.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22There%20are%20five%20special%20classrooms%20and%20seven%20classrooms%20with%20individual%20courtyards%20in%20the%20school.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-6-1706623850.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-6-1706623850-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-6-1706623850-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-6-1706623850-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-6-1706623850-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-340126%5